://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/home">Google Webmaster Tools</a>, use the HTML tag selected. Google will create an HTML statement on the setup page. From this instruction, you copy the component specified in the content attribute. <br> Example: <br> Google returns the HTML code: &nbsp; &nbsp; <code> &lt; meta name="google-site-verification" content="BBssyCpddd8" / &gt; </code> <br> Then enter this: <code> BBssyCpddd8 </code>.
